He/she doesn't need to have your name, but if not, make sure you remember which person you are. Two ways to create people are:
Make a folder with their name so that you can show what they are "holding," much like an inventory. You can also change the icon of the folder with downloaded sprites or pictures of people so that they can have identities. If you need to turn pictures into icons, you can download an icon-making program. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e1\/Create-a-City-or-Town-on-Your-Computer-Step-6Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-City-or-Town-on-Your-Computer-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/e\/e1\/Create-a-City-or-Town-on-Your-Computer-Step-6Bullet1.jpg\/aid211873-v4-728px-Create-a-City-or-Town-on-Your-Computer-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":337,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"534","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Make a Word document or textbook file and keep track of what they own, their jobs, relationships, what they think, etc. on it.
